        "Certificate of Undergraduate Study in Middle School Mathematics": [
            "Certificate of Undergraduate Study in Middle School Mathematics The Certificate of Undergraduate Study (CUGS) in Middle School Mathematics (5-8) provides a broad-based practice in the study of mathematics e.g. statistics, geometry, and algebraic thinking that complement courses in elementary education while enabling students to pursue certification in Middle School Mathematics. The teacher candidate will acquire specialized knowledge on building mathematical ideas and experiences drawing from connections and relationships with mathematics they learned in elementary school."
        ],
