                "Total Credits in Program: 16-17 s.h. To be awarded the CUGS in Middle School Mathematics, students must complete all courses required for the B.A. in Elementary Education program in addition to the CUGS in Middle School Mathematics with at least a 3.0 (C-) in all coursework. **These courses require that students pass the CLM portion of the Accu-placer test or are SAT exempt. Additional testing and fees required for 5-8th grade Math state certification if they pursue this CUGS. Erica Watson Brown Program Coordinator James Hall 3057 856.256.3812 watsonbrown@rowan.edu",
